textBody:
Dutch Limburg may refer to the following:
* Limburg (Netherlands) (1866–present), a province of the Netherlands
* Duchy of Limburg (1839–1867), a duchy in personal union with the Kingdom of the Netherlands
* Province of Limburg (1815–1839), a province of the former United Kingdom of the Netherlands
* Limburg of the States, territories controlled by the Dutch States-General from 1648 to 1794 as Generality Lands
